<paragraph id="4BC8EE7606C238B354686DED06A7CBF6" pageId="9" pageNumber="24">know only from two Ethiopian localities, more than 200 km apart.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A4865F343716C0EA6B18973DC9387B67" pageId="9" pageNumber="24" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="0D25F2BCBE99342880D7522D5B816155" pageId="9" pageNumber="24">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F521689A228E6D09C0FA17BCE0AE2DB7" pageId="9" pageNumber="24">
The pedipalp chela length-to-width ratio given by the author for the type material suggest that some animals exhibit sexual dimorphism while others do not. If this is true, the utility of this ratio as a diagnostic character in 
<taxonomicName id="4F39F8836E977C747E79DB217360F586" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Buthus" order="Scorpiones" pageId="9" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Buthus</taxonomicName>
would be compromised. Alternatively, it may be due simply to the use of immature specimens.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
